Introduction

Base URL: http://api.moboeats.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Authentication Management

User API resource

Login through email and password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"bpfeffer@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"ri[0d[\",
    \"userType\": \"laudantium\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "bpfeffer@example.com",
    "password": "ri[0d[",
    "userType": "laudantium"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

The email of the user Example: bpfeffer@example.com

password   string   

The password of the user Example: ri[0d[

userType   string   

The type of user Example: laudantium

Registration

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"audoqujecfzgnyge\",
    \"email\": \"ekautzer@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"p>@Mmu}V\",
    \"userType\": \"autem\",
    \"phone\": \"dolores\",
    \"latitude\": \"labore\",
    \"longitude\": \"facilis\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "audoqujecfzgnyge",
    "email": "ekautzer@example.net",
    "password": "p>@Mmu}V",
    "userType": "autem",
    "phone": "dolores",
    "latitude": "labore",
    "longitude": "facilis"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: audoqujecfzgnyge

email   string   

The email of the user Example: ekautzer@example.net

password   string   

The password of the user Example: p>@Mmu}V

userType   string   

The type of user Example: autem

otp   string  optional  
image   string  optional  
phone   string   

The type of user Example: dolores

latitude   string  optional  

optional The latitude of the user. Example -1.2847473 Example: labore

longitude   string  optional  

optional The longitude of the user. Example 36.3878745 Example: facilis

Forgot Password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/forgot-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"tyrell.ondricka@example.org\",
    \"phone_number\": \"odit\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/forgot-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "tyrell.ondricka@example.org",
    "phone_number": "odit"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.

Reset password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"code\": \"ipsam\",
    \"password\": \"VSSuOk6\\/*0OzqpJ{c\",
    \"password_confirmation\": \"recusandae\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "code": "ipsam",
    "password": "VSSuOk6\/*0OzqpJ{c",
    "password_confirmation": "recusandae"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/reset-password

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

code   The  optional  

Verification OTP code Example: ipsam

password   The  optional  

new password to be set Example: VSSuOk6/*0OzqpJ{c

password_confirmation   The  optional  

new password confirmation Example: recusandae

Request      

POST api/v2/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

phone_number   string   

The phone number of the user. Example 44374673827 Example: rerum

device_token   string  optional  

optional The device token Example: et

latitude   string  optional  

optional The latitude of the user. Example -1.2847473 Example: voluptas

longitude   string  optional  

optional The longitude of the user. Example 36.3878745 Example: qui

Verify OTP

curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v2/login/otp/verify" \

    \"code\": \"qui\",
    \"userType\": \"odit\"
}"

Logout

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/logout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {

    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/menu"
);

The id of the menu item Example: 2

menu_rating   integer   

The rating of the menu from 1 - 5 Example: 12

menu_review   string  optional  

A review of the menu Example: dolores

order_id   integer  optional  

The id of the order Example: 7

Display a listing of the menus.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/restaurant/menu?categories=laboriosam&subCategories=sit&restaurant=alias" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/restaurant/menu"
);

const params = {
    "categories": "laboriosam",
    "subCategories": "sit",
    "restaurant": "alias",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Create Rider Profile

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "vehicle_type=dicta" \
    --form "vehicle_license_plate=quam" \
    --form "paypal_email=evans24@example.com" \
    --form "vehicle_licesne_plate=sunt" \
    --form "city=nihil" \
    --form "state=illum" \
    --form "postal_code=et" \
    --form "profile_picture=@C:\Users\Lenovo\AppData\Local\Temp\php6E1.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('vehicle_type', 'dicta');
body.append('vehicle_license_plate', 'quam');
body.append('paypal_email', 'evans24@example.com');
body.append('vehicle_licesne_plate', 'sunt');
body.append('city', 'nihil');
body.append('state', 'illum');
body.append('postal_code', 'et');
body.append('profile_picture', document.querySelector('input[name="profile_picture"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

Display listing of supplement categories

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/orderer/supplements/categories?search=autem&perPage=4" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/orderer/supplements/categories"
);

const params = {
    "search": "autem",
    "perPage": "4",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

}"

);
